## Adding a native module — short version

When you (the agent) add a new native module via `expo install <pkg>`:

1. Top-level `import` it like any other module.
2. Tell the user *"Adding `<pkg>` — native module, so the next ship is a full `eas build`, not an OTA."*
3. Bump the version per §B4 and run the full build flow.
4. No shim. No lazy-require. No feature-detect. The app simply doesn't have that capability until the next binary lands.

