### Cancelling a build

```bash
eas build:cancel <build-id>
```

### Build profiles

| Profile | Use case | Status |
|---------|----------|--------|
| `development` | Metro-attached dev-client build for fast JS iteration on a real device | Use for chip-bar / map / any heavy iteration work |
| `preview` | Internal testing on devices (ad-hoc .ipa) | **Default for distribution / demo** |
| `production` | App Store / Play Store submission | Use `eas submit` after |

The `development` profile was removed 2026-04-25 and restored 2026-05-21 (v2.5.0) when the map / chip-bar iteration loop became too painful via OTA. If a future cleanup wants to remove it again, also remove `expo-dev-client` from `package.json` in the same change so the profile doesn't bit-rot in `eas.json`.

### Current Version

**2.5.6 — build 24 (iOS Google Maps fix: react-native-maps config plugin entry + dep bump 1.20.1 → 1.27.2)** — cut 2026-05-25. v2.5.5 build 23 set `ios.config.googleMapsApiKey` in `app.config.js` but did NOT add `"react-native-maps"` to the `plugins` array, so the native iOS build linked the Apple-Maps-only variant of `react-native-maps`. Runtime logged `react-native-maps: AirGoogleMaps dir must be added to your xCode project to support GoogleMaps on iOS` on every `<MapView provider={PROVIDER_GOOGLE}>` render, and the map showed an error overlay instead of tiles. This build (a) bumps `react-native-maps` from `1.20.1` → `1.27.2` because the config plugin (`app.plugin.js`) only ships on `react-native-maps@1.22+`, and (b) adds the missing `["react-native-maps", { iosGoogleMapsApiKey }]` plugin entry, which triggers Expo's prebuild step to inject AirGoogleMaps into the Podfile. Both pieces (the `ios.config.googleMapsApiKey` from build 23 AND the new plugin entry) are required. The plugin's `iosGoogleMapsApiKey` option is set defensively alongside the ios.config one because both write `GMSApiKey` to Info.plist; with the same value it's idempotent. Expo's compatibility matrix still pins `react-native-maps@1.20.1` for SDK 54, but that's stale matrix data — the upstream 1.27.x line ships the SDK-53+ plugin that Expo's own MapView docs assume exists. Native config change + native dep bump requires the full build per Step 0c (or a local `npx expo run:ios --device` rebuild — see below). Bump from here for the next build. OTA updates should target this runtime version.

**Local rebuild path (no EAS):** for this kind of native-config-only change, `npx expo run:ios --device` is equivalent to `eas build --profile development --platform ios` but runs on your Mac (no EAS credit, ~15 min cold). It does `expo prebuild` → `pod install` → `xcodebuild` → installs the resulting dev-client `.app` onto the connected iPhone → connects to your existing Metro at :8081. Subsequent JS edits still hot-reload via Metro just like a cloud-built dev-client. The auto-generated `ios/` directory is gitignored (CNG pattern). Use the EAS path instead when you need an IPA to distribute (preview / production profiles).

The historical build log (which version shipped on what date, which native modules it linked) lives in [`docs/BUILD-LOG.md`](../../docs/BUILD-LOG.md). Step B8 of the full-build path appends a new entry there, not here.
